CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779984666
OL,3,CO'Neill signs contract extension to
OL,4,Cremain as NI manager
OL,6,FO'Neill, who led Northern Ireland to
OL,7,FEuro 2016, is in his second stint in
OL,8,Fcharge of the national team, having
OL,9,Foverseen a record 104 matches. First
OL,10,Fappointed in 2011, O'Neill left for
OL,11,FStoke in 2020 but returned in 2022.
OL,13,FAfter his new contract was announced,
OL,14,FO'Neill named a 23-strong squad for
OL,15,Fnext month's friendlies against Guinea
OL,16,Fand France, handing first call-ups to
OL,17,FEverton youngster Braiden Graham and
OL,18,FArsenal prospect Ceadach O'Neill, both
OL,19,F18, in a squad which is missing
OL,20,Fseveral senior players.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
